description:
Role / Responsibilities

The Clinical Scientist will provide scientific and clinical expertise and play a key leadership role in the JTX-8064 anti-LILRB2 program and other novel programs targeting tumor associated myeloid cells. The successful candidate will be a member of the clinical development team and the JTX-8064 Program Team, working closely with colleagues in medical affairs, biostats and... programming, clinical pharmacology, translational science, clinical operations, drug safety, new product planning, and product leadership to support clinical development strategy and execution of all JTX-8064 clinical trials.

The Clinical Scientist is responsible for contributing to program strategy, leading development of protocols and amendments, analyzing, interpreting, and presenting clinical study data and ensuring adherence to Jounce SOPs, GCP, and regulatory requirements.

Responsibilities
• Contribute to the clinical strategy and creation of the clinical development plans for various oncology indications;
• Lead development of clinical study protocols and amendments, obtaining appropriate cross-functional input on study design, objectives, endpoints and eligibility criteria;
• Provide clinical and at times operational oversight of study execution in collaboration with clinical operations and medical affairs;
• Contribute to the development of program documents, including the clinical sections of various regulatory documents such as IND, clinical study reports, investigator brochures, annual reports and updates, and clinical sections of regulatory submissions to support product approvals;
• Collaborate with data management, biostats, and programming to ensure eCRF design supports optimal and adequate data collection in accordance with the study protocol and regulatory requirements;
• Collaborate with clinical development, biostats, programming, clinical pharmacology, data management, drug safety, and translational science on the review, analysis, and interpretation of study results and assure appropriate data review and accurate data reporting;
• Reviewing and monitor emerging clinical data related to safety and efficacy. Develop strategic and practical solutions to any issues identified and work with clinical operations to ensure issue resolution;
• Work closely with the medical monitor to assure he/she is informed of pertinent study information, including but not limited to safety and efficacy data;
• Contribute to and participate in Dose escalation activities and Data and Safety Monitoring Committee meetings, as needed;
• Develop presentations and communicates study data results to Jounce Portfolio Steering Team and Board of Directors and to external audiences including investigators at sponsor meetings or general audiences at scientific conferences;
• Prepare data for various presentations including peer-reviewed publications;
• Maintain current knowledge of the competitive landscape to ensure emerging changes are incorporated into clinical trial development strategy;
• Solid understanding of therapeutic and disease-specific standard-of-care and emerging therapies;
• Work as part of a highly matrixed organization; and
• Work with Head of MSL team to create training documents and provide disease state, protocol, and relevant translational science training to MSLs.

Qualifications
• MD, NP, MS, PhD or PharmD, or equivalent with clinical research experience. Advanced degree candidates preferred;
• At least 5 years of clinical, technical/operational experience in planning, executing, reporting and publishing clinical studies, basic knowledge of ICH/GCP;
• Strong analytical scientific background with industry clinical development experience in oncology;
• Effective communication and influencing skills;
• Fluency in the English language, both written and verbal;
• Thorough understanding of the drug development process from pre-IND through registration and post-registration required;
• Broad understanding of functional areas of drug development, including preclinical/translational, regulatory, pharmacovigilance, data management, biostatistics, programming, and clinical operations;
• Ability to understand, interpret and communicate clinical information including literature reviews, competitive intelligence, and changing treatment paradigms;
• Understanding of trial design and statistics in order to apply knowledge to the design of clinical protocols;
• Ability to interpret, analyze, and present clinical;
• Critical traits for success include strategic and proactive thinking, strong scientific and analytical skills, detail-oriented, decisiveness and the ability to perform as a collaborative team member and leader;
• Ability to work independently and to organize priorities and deliverables; and
• Ability to work in an environment with high expectations for achievement.

Statement

Diversity and Inclusion Statement

Jounce strives to create a workplace that reflects the diversity of cancer patients, and where all feel included and valued because of their differences. Actively including people who add to our culture and enhance our values leads to better decisions and outcomes for those we serve – patients, all patients. Beyond our walls, our focus is on addressing inequities in opportunities for STEM education, careers opportunities in Biotech, and access to cancer care.

Equal Opportunity Employer

Jounce Therapeutics is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate in its employment decisions on the basis of race, color, national origin, age, physical or mental disability, marital status, religion, creed, sex, or political beliefs. We offer a competitive salary and benefits package. All applicants should be legally entitled to work for any employer in the U.S.

Company Summary

Jounce Therapeutics, Inc. is a clinical-stage immunotherapy company dedicated to transforming the treatment of cancer by developing therapies that enable the immune system to attack tumors and provide long-lasting benefits to patients through a biomarker-driven approach. Jounce currently has multiple development stage programs ongoing while simultaneously advancing additional early-stage assets from its robust discovery engine based on its Translational Science Platform. Jounce’s highest priority program, JTX-8064, is a LILRB2 (ILT4) receptor antagonist shown to reprogram immune-suppressive tumor associated macrophages to an anti-tumor state in preclinical studies. A Phase 1 clinical trial, named INNATE, for JTX-8064 as a monotherapy and in combination with JTX-4014, Jounce’s internal PD-1 inhibitor, or pembrolizumab is currently enrolling patients with advanced solid tumors. Jounce’s most advanced product candidate, vopratelimab, is a monoclonal antibody that binds to and activates ICOS, and is currently being studied in the SELECT Phase 2 trial. JTX-4014 is a PD-1 inhibitor intended for combination use in the INNATE and SELECT trials and with Jounce’s broader pipeline. Additionally, Jounce exclusively licensed worldwide rights to JTX-1811, a monoclonal antibody targeting CCR8 and designed to selectively deplete T regulatory cells in the tumor microenvironment, to Gilead Sciences, Inc
